cs.RO, cs.ME, cs.SY, cs.CV, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper is about designing and optimizing quad-robots with soft skins, and developing a motion control strategy for them. 
- cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering) is also likely as the paper involves modeling the multibody dynamics of the mechanical skeleton and the elastic behavior of the soft skin. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper discusses the motion control strategy and optimization scheme used to drive the robot to achieve a user prescribed motion trajectory. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions using empirical manufacturing guidance to support the fabrication of the designed quad-robot. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also less likely but possible as the paper may involve visualizing the designed quad-robots and their motion trajectories.
